{#
  Hub / index page for the per-SDN research dossier corpus.
  Served from /research/sdn/ — targets the head terms (OFAC SDN
  research, OFAC SDN search, sanctions EDD) that the per-slug
  dossier pages do not. Card grid + cluster nav + comparison block
  positions dossiers as a different product from the lighter
  /sanctions/individuals/<slug> profile pages, so Google sees them
  as complementary rather than competing.
#}
{% extends "_base.html.j2" %}

{% block head_extra %}
<style>
  .research-hub { max-width: 1100px; margin: 24px auto 64px; padding: 0 24px; }

  .research-hub .breadcrumbs {
    font-size: 12px; color: #5a6478;
    margin-bottom: 18px;
  }
  .research-hub .breadcrumbs a { color: #5a6478; text-decoration: none; }
  .research-hub .breadcrumbs a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  .research-hub .breadcrumbs strong { color: #1a2b3d; }

  .hub-hero {
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #f4f8fc 0%, #fff 100%);
    border-left: 4px solid #002b5e;
    padding: 28px 32px;
    margin: 0 0 36px;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }
  .hub-hero .eyebrow {
    font-size: 11px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 1.6px;
    color: #002b5e;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .hub-hero h1 {
    font-size: 32px;
    line-height: 1.15;
    margin: 0 0 14px;
    color: #0a1828;
    letter-spacing: -0.5px;
  }
  .hub-hero .lede {
    font-size: 16.5px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: #2a3645;
    margin: 0 0 16px;
    max-width: 760px;
  }
  .hub-hero .stats {
    display: flex; gap: 28px; flex-wrap: wrap;
    font-size: 13px; color: #4a5468;
    padding-top: 14px;
    border-top: 1px solid #e1e8f0;
  }
  .hub-hero .stats strong { color: #002b5e; font-weight: 700; }

  /* Comparison block — the core differentiator vs /sanctions/individuals/ */
  .vs-block {
    margin: 0 0 44px;
    border: 1px solid #d8e0eb;
    border-radius: 4px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .vs-block h2 {
    font-size: 18px;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 14px 20px;
    background: #f4f8fc;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #d8e0eb;
    color: #0a1828;
  }
  .vs-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 0;
  }
  .vs-col { padding: 20px 24px; }
  .vs-col + .vs-col { border-left: 1px solid #d8e0eb; }
  .vs-col .vs-eyebrow {
    font-size: 10.5px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 1.4px;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  .vs-col.profile .vs-eyebrow { color: #6a7484; }
  .vs-col.dossier .vs-eyebrow { color: #002b5e; }
  .vs-col .vs-title {
    font-size: 16px; font-weight: 700; color: #0a1828;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }
  .vs-col .vs-url { font-size: 12px; color: #6a7484; font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace; margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .vs-col .vs-tagline { font-size: 14px; color: #2a3645; line-height: 1.55; margin: 0 0 14px; font-style: italic; }
  .vs-col ul { padding-left: 18px; margin: 0 0 14px; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.6; color: #2a3645; }
  .vs-col ul li { margin-bottom: 4px; }
  .vs-col .vs-best { font-size: 13px; color: #4a5468; }
  .vs-col .vs-best strong { color: #0a1828; }

  .vs-col.dossier { background: #fafcfe; }

  /* Cluster nav (jump-to-section) */
  .cluster-nav {
    display: flex; gap: 8px; flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin: 0 0 28px;
    padding: 12px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #e1e8f0;
  }
  .cluster-nav .label {
    font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 1.4px;
    color: #6a7484; font-weight: 600;
    align-self: center; margin-right: 6px;
  }
  .cluster-nav a {
    font-size: 13px;
    padding: 5px 12px;
    border: 1px solid #cfddee;
    border-radius: 99px;
    background: #fff;
    color: #002b5e;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .cluster-nav a:hover { background: #002b5e; color: #fff; }
  .cluster-nav .count {
    font-size: 11px;
    margin-left: 6px;
    opacity: 0.7;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  /* Cluster sections */
  .cluster {
    margin: 0 0 36px;
    scroll-margin-top: 90px;
  }
  .cluster-header {
    display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 12px;
    margin: 0 0 14px;
    padding-bottom: 10px;
    border-bottom: 2px solid #002b5e;
  }
  .cluster-header h2 {
    font-size: 22px; margin: 0; color: #0a1828; letter-spacing: -0.3px;
  }
  .cluster-header .cluster-meta {
    font-size: 13px; color: #6a7484;
  }

  /* Card grid */
  .card-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(320px, 1fr));
    gap: 16px;
  }
  .dossier-card {
    border: 1px solid #d8e0eb;
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 18px 20px;
    background: #fff;
    transition: border-color 0.15s, box-shadow 0.15s, transform 0.15s;
    display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 10px;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
  }
  .dossier-card:hover {
    border-color: #002b5e;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 16px rgba(0, 43, 94, 0.08);
    transform: translateY(-1px);
  }
  .dossier-card .dc-status {
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px;
    font-size: 10.5px; font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 1.2px;
    color: #cc0000;
  }
  .dossier-card .dc-status::before {
    content: ""; display: inline-block;
    width: 8px; height: 8px; border-radius: 50%; background: #cc0000;
  }
  .dossier-card h3 {
    font-size: 17px;
    margin: 0;
    color: #0a1828;
    line-height: 1.25;
    font-weight: 700;
  }
  .dossier-card .dc-raw {
    font-size: 11.5px;
    color: #6a7484;
    font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace;
  }
  .dossier-card .dc-tagline {
    font-size: 13.5px;
    color: #2a3645;
    line-height: 1.5;
    flex: 1;
  }
  .dossier-card .dc-meta {
    display: flex; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap;
    font-size: 11.5px; color: #5a6478;
    padding-top: 10px;
    border-top: 1px solid #eef2f7;
  }
  .dossier-card .dc-meta strong { color: #1a2b3d; font-weight: 600; }
  .dossier-card .dc-cta {
    font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600;
    color: #002b5e;
    margin-top: 4px;
  }
  .dossier-card .dc-cta::after { content: " →"; }

  /* FAQ block */
  .hub-faq {
    margin: 48px 0 0;
    padding-top: 32px;
    border-top: 1px solid #e1e8f0;
  }
  .hub-faq h2 {
    font-size: 22px; margin: 0 0 18px; color: #0a1828; letter-spacing: -0.3px;
  }
  .hub-faq .faq-item {
    border-top: 1px solid #eef2f7;
    padding: 16px 0;
  }
  .hub-faq .faq-item:first-child { border-top: none; }
  .hub-faq .faq-q { font-weight: 700; font-size: 15px; color: #0a1828; margin: 0 0 6px; }
  .hub-faq .faq-a { font-size: 14.5px; color: #2a3645; line-height: 1.65; margin: 0; }
  .hub-faq .faq-a a { color: #002b5e; font-weight: 600; }

  /* Methodology box */
  .hub-method {
    margin: 32px 0 0;
    padding: 20px 24px;
    background: #f4f8fc;
    border: 1px solid #d8e0eb;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }
  .hub-method h2 { font-size: 18px; margin: 0 0 10px; color: #0a1828; }
  .hub-method p { font-size: 14px; color: #2a3645; line-height: 1.65; margin: 0 0 8px; }
  .hub-method ol { font-size: 14px; color: #2a3645; line-height: 1.65; padding-left: 22px; margin: 0; }
  .hub-method ol li { margin-bottom: 4px; }

  @media (max-width: 700px) {
    .vs-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .vs-col + .vs-col { border-left: none; border-top: 1px solid #d8e0eb; }
    .hub-hero h1 { font-size: 26px; }
    .hub-hero { padding: 22px 20px; }
  }
</style>
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
<div class="research-hub">
  <nav class="breadcrumbs" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
    <a href="/">Home</a> <span>›</span>
    <strong>OFAC SDN Research Dossiers</strong>
  </nav>

  {# ── Hero / lede ───────────────────────────────────────────────── #}
  <section class="hub-hero">
    <div class="eyebrow">OFAC SDN · Due-Diligence Research</div>
    <h1>OFAC SDN Research Dossiers</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      Hand-curated due-diligence dossiers on individuals on the US Treasury
      <strong>Specially Designated Nationals (SDN) list</strong> — built for
      compliance teams, EDD analysts, and KYC reviewers who need more than
      a yes/no status check before adding a name to an evidence file.
      Each dossier disambiguates the entity from same-surname siblings and
      look-alikes, links the underlying OFAC press release and Executive
      Order, surfaces adverse media, and exports as a tamper-evident PDF.
    </p>
    <div class="stats">
      <span><strong>{{ total_dossiers }}</strong> dossiers</span>
      <span><strong>{{ clusters|length }}</strong> name clusters</span>
      <span>Source data: <strong>OFAC SDN list</strong> (US Treasury)</span>
      <span>Updated: <strong>continuously</strong></span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="cr-search-panel" role="search" aria-label="Search OFAC SDN research dossiers">
    <label class="cr-search-label" for="dossier-search">Search dossiers</label>
    <div class="cr-search-row">
      <input type="search" id="dossier-search" placeholder="Search a name, raw OFAC name, program, or role…" autocomplete="off">
    </div>
    <p class="cr-search-help">Use this first when you know the name. Results below filter instantly across every dossier card.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="cr-empty-filter" id="dossier-empty">No dossiers match that search.</div>

  {# ── How a dossier differs from a sanctions profile ────────────── #}
  <section class="vs-block" aria-labelledby="vs-heading">
    <h2 id="vs-heading">Dossier vs. sanctions profile — when to use which</h2>
    <div class="vs-grid">
      <div class="vs-col profile">
        <div class="vs-eyebrow">Lighter — Sanctions profile</div>
        <div class="vs-title">Sanctions profile page</div>
        <div class="vs-url">/sanctions/individuals/&lt;slug&gt;</div>
        <p class="vs-tagline">
          One auto-generated page per OFAC SDN entry — every individual,
          entity, vessel, and aircraft on the list.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Active SDN status, program, designation date</li>
          <li>Identity card from the OFAC record</li>
          <li>Co-designated family + linked-to entities</li>
          <li>Recent related news from our index</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="vs-best">
          <strong>Best for:</strong> a 30-second status check —
          <em>"is this person currently sanctioned?"</em>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="vs-col dossier">
        <div class="vs-eyebrow">Deeper — Research dossier</div>
        <div class="vs-title">Research dossier page</div>
        <div class="vs-url">/research/sdn/&lt;slug&gt;</div>
        <p class="vs-tagline">
          A hand-curated, citation-grade research file — produced for
          high-stakes names where the lighter profile page is not enough.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Same-surname <strong>disambiguation strip</strong> — answers
            "<em>is this my Saab?</em>" in one screen</li>
          <li>Plain-English <strong>"why designated"</strong> narrative grounded
            in OFAC primary sources</li>
          <li>The actual <strong>OFAC press release</strong> + underlying
            Executive Order, deep-linked</li>
          <li>Curated <strong>adverse media</strong> + live Google News pull,
            de-duplicated</li>
          <li>Corporate-affiliation jumps (OpenCorporates, ICIJ Offshore
            Leaks, OpenSanctions, Sunbiz, LinkedIn)</li>
          <li><strong>Tamper-evident PDF export</strong> with SHA-256
            fingerprint — drop-in for an EDD memo</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="vs-best">
          <strong>Best for:</strong> producing the evidence file —
          <em>"build the EDD memo."</em>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {# ── Cluster jump nav ──────────────────────────────────────────── #}
  {% if clusters|length > 1 %}
  <nav class="cluster-nav" aria-label="Jump to surname group">
    <span class="label">Jump to surname</span>
    {% for cluster in clusters %}
      <a href="#{{ cluster.key|lower|replace(' ', '-') }}">
        {{ cluster.label }}<span class="count">({{ cluster.cards|length }})</span>
      </a>
    {% endfor %}
  </nav>
  {% endif %}

  {# ── Card grid grouped by cluster ──────────────────────────────── #}
  {% for cluster in clusters %}
  <section class="cluster" id="{{ cluster.key|lower|replace(' ', '-') }}">
    <header class="cluster-header">
      <h2>{{ cluster.label }} family</h2>
      <span class="cluster-meta">
        {{ cluster.cards|length }} dossier{{ '' if cluster.cards|length == 1 else 's' }} sharing this surname
      </span>
    </header>
    <div class="card-grid">
      {% for c in cluster.cards %}
      <a class="dossier-card" href="{{ c.url }}" data-search="{{ (c.display_name ~ ' ' ~ c.raw_name ~ ' ' ~ c.program ~ ' ' ~ c.program_code ~ ' ' ~ (c.public_role or '') ~ ' ' ~ c.tagline)|lower }}">
        <span class="dc-status">Active SDN</span>
        <h3>{{ c.display_name }}</h3>
        <div class="dc-raw">{{ c.raw_name }}</div>
        <p class="dc-tagline">{{ c.tagline }}</p>
        <div class="dc-meta">
          <span><strong>Program:</strong> {{ c.program_code }}</span>
          {% if c.designation_date %}
          <span><strong>Designated:</strong> {{ c.designation_date }}</span>
          {% endif %}
        </div>
        <span class="dc-cta">Open dossier</span>
      </a>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </section>
  {% endfor %}

  {# ── FAQ — explicitly targets the head queries ─────────────────── #}
  <section class="hub-faq" aria-labelledby="faq-heading">
    <h2 id="faq-heading">Frequently asked</h2>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <p class="faq-q">Why use this instead of the official OFAC SDN search?</p>
      <p class="faq-a">
        The Treasury <a href="https://sanctionssearch.ofac.treas.gov/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">SDN search tool</a>
        gives you the raw record — name, programs, identifiers, "Linked To"
        line items. It does not disambiguate same-surname designees, link to
        the press release, surface adverse media, or produce a portable
        evidence file. These dossiers do all of that, with primary-source
        citations, in a one-page format you can paste into an EDD memo
        or hand to a regulator.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <p class="faq-q">How is a dossier different from your existing sanctions profile pages?</p>
      <p class="faq-a">
        The <a href="/sanctions-tracker">sanctions profile pages</a> exist for
        every OFAC SDN entry and are auto-generated from the underlying record —
        ideal for a quick status check. The dossiers are hand-curated for a
        smaller set of high-stakes names where ambiguity, look-alikes, or
        public scrutiny justify a deeper file. Where both exist for a person,
        the profile page links to the dossier and vice versa — they are
        complementary, not duplicate.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <p class="faq-q">Are these dossiers admissible / suitable for an EDD or compliance memo?</p>
      <p class="faq-a">
        They are intended as a research aid, not as a substitute for
        primary-source verification. Every claim links back to its source
        (OFAC entry, press release, executive order, news article); the PDF
        export carries a SHA-256 content fingerprint so any later
        modification of the underlying record is detectable. Compliance teams
        typically attach the dossier PDF as supporting evidence and cite
        the primary OFAC record as the authoritative source.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <p class="faq-q">Why are profiles grouped by surname?</p>
      <p class="faq-a">
        Two of the most-searched OFAC names — <em>Saab</em> and <em>Carretero</em> —
        each appear on the SDN list multiple times. <strong>Alex Nain Saab Moran</strong>
        (Maduro's frontman) is routinely confused with his siblings and with
        <strong>Tarek William Saab Halabi</strong> (Venezuela's sitting Attorney
        General, no familial relation). Grouping the dossiers by surname makes
        the disambiguation visible at a glance.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <p class="faq-q">Can I request a dossier on someone not yet listed?</p>
      <p class="faq-a">
        Dossiers are added based on observed search demand and editorial
        judgment about disambiguation risk. If a name you need is on the OFAC
        SDN list but does not yet have a dossier, the
        <a href="/sanctions-tracker">sanctions profile page</a> for that
        person is published the same day OFAC adds them, and is fully
        searchable on this site.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  {# ── Methodology block ─────────────────────────────────────────── #}
  <section class="hub-method" aria-labelledby="method-heading">
    <h2 id="method-heading">How we build a dossier</h2>
    <p>
      Each dossier is assembled from publicly available primary sources. No
      paywalled data, no leaked records, no unverified claims.
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li>Pull the canonical OFAC SDN record (program, designation date, identifiers, Linked-To set).</li>
      <li>Add the matching <strong>OFAC press release</strong> and the underlying <strong>Executive Order</strong> as primary sources.</li>
      <li>Build the <strong>same-surname disambiguator</strong> from co-listed SDN names, with full identity-card detail on each.</li>
      <li>Pull <strong>adverse media</strong> from Google News (24-hour cache), de-duplicated against curated items.</li>
      <li>Generate the plain-English <strong>"why designated"</strong> narrative from the OFAC primary-source set, using a strict, anti-hallucination prompt.</li>
      <li>Compute a <strong>SHA-256 content fingerprint</strong> of the underlying record so the PDF export is tamper-evident.</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

</div>
<script>
(function () {
  var input = document.getElementById('dossier-search');
  var empty = document.getElementById('dossier-empty');
  if (!input) return;
  var clusters = Array.prototype.slice.call(document.querySelectorAll('.cluster'));
  input.addEventListener('input', function () {
    var q = input.value.trim().toLowerCase();
    var totalVisible = 0;
    clusters.forEach(function (cluster) {
      var visibleInCluster = 0;
      Array.prototype.slice.call(cluster.querySelectorAll('.dossier-card[data-search]')).forEach(function (card) {
        var show = !q || (card.getAttribute('data-search') || '').indexOf(q) !== -1;
        card.style.display = show ? '' : 'none';
        if (show) visibleInCluster += 1;
      });
      totalVisible += visibleInCluster;
      cluster.style.display = visibleInCluster ? '' : 'none';
    });
    if (empty) empty.style.display = q && totalVisible === 0 ? 'block' : 'none';
  });
})();
</script>
{# JSON-LD is rendered by _base.html.j2 via the `jsonld` template var. #}
{% endblock %}
